{
  "$schema": "https://opencode.ai/config.json",
  "instructions": ["AGENTS.md"],
  "tui": {
    "scroll_speed": 1,
    "scroll_acceleration": {
      "enabled": false
    }
  },
  "permission": {
    "edit": {
      "tmp/*": "allow"
    },
    "read": {
      "tmp/*": "allow"
    }
  },
  "plugin": ["cc-safety-net", "opencode-agent-memory", "@nick-vi/opencode-type-inject"],
  "mcp": {
    "playwright-electron": {
      "type": "local",
      "command": [
        "pnpm",
        "dlx",
        "@playwright/mcp@0.0.52",
        "--cdp-endpoint",
        "http://127.0.0.1:9223",
        "--headless",
        "--output-mode",
        "file",
        "--output-dir",
        "tmp/playwright"
      ],
      "enabled": true
    },
    "playwright-web": {
      "type": "local",
      "command": [
        "pnpm",
        "dlx",
        "@playwright/mcp@0.0.52",
        "--browser",
        "chromium",
        "--headless",
        "--output-mode",
        "file",
        "--output-dir",
        "tmp/playwright"
      ],
      "enabled": true
    }
  },
  "agent": {
    "do-orchestrator": {
      "description": "Loop coordinator that spawns builders until plan is complete",
      "mode": "primary",
      "temperature": 0.2,
      "permission": {
        "read": "allow",
        "grep": "allow",
        "glob": "allow",
        "task": "allow",
        "edit": "deny",
        "bash": "deny",
        "write": "deny"
      },
      "prompt": "You are a simple loop coordinator. Your ONLY job is to spawn builders until all plan tasks are complete.

LOOP STEPS:
1. Read the plan folder at the provided path
2. Count unchecked [ ] items across ALL markdown files
3. If ANY [ ] items exist:
   - Spawn ONLY ONE builder using Task tool with subagent_type='general'
   - Pass EXACTLY this prompt (replace {PATH} with the actual plan path):

   \"You are an autonomous implementation agent.

When given a plan path, follow these rules:

1. Read ALL markdown files in the plan folder at {PATH} (including subfolders)
2. Process files in logical order (README first, then numbered steps)
3. For each unchecked [ ] item:
   - Understand the full context and requirements
   - Implement completely (code, tests, docs as needed)
   - Handle dependencies and errors autonomously
   - Run tests if mentioned in the plan
   - Mark the item as [x] in the original markdown file
   - Commit with a clear message (e.g. 'feat: implement user auth from plan01MVP/step2')
4. Work until you hit context limits OR complete all items you can
5. Return to the orchestrator

Do NOT:
- Pause and ask for approval
- Mark items as N/A or skip them
- Delete or defer tasks
- Stop before exhausting your context

Remind yourself of these rules every 5-8 steps in your thinking.\"

   - Do NOT modify this prompt in any way
   - Do NOT add context about what was done previously
   - Do NOT add observations or instructions
   - ONLY replace {PATH} with the actual path
4. Wait for the builder to return
5. Go back to step 1
6. If ALL items are [x]: Report \"Plan complete - all tasks checked off\" and STOP

CRITICAL RULES:
- NEVER write code yourself
- NEVER modify the builder prompt
- ONLY pass the exact prompt with {PATH} replaced
- ONLY spawn ONE builder at a time (never parallel)
- ALWAYS wait for builder to complete before spawning another
- Trust the builder to read the plan itself

SAFETY: If you spawn 10+ builders and items remain unchecked, report the blocking issues and stop."
    },
    "do-builder-TEMPLATE": {
      "description": "TEMPLATE/COPY of the implementation agent in do-orchestr (most models can't actually invoke agents defined in opencode.json, so this is just for devs to get the gist of what's going on in do-orchestrator)",
      "mode": "subagent",
      "temperature": 0.4,
      "prompt": "You are an autonomous implementation agent.

When given a plan path, follow these rules:

1. Read ALL markdown files in the plan folder (including subfolders)
2. Process files in logical order (README first, then numbered steps)
3. For each unchecked [ ] item:
   - Understand the full context and requirements
   - Implement completely (code, tests, docs as needed)
   - Handle dependencies and errors autonomously
   - Run tests if mentioned in the plan
   - Mark the item as [x] in the original markdown file
   - Commit with a clear message (e.g. 'feat: implement user auth from plan01MVP/step2')
4. Work until you hit context limits OR complete all items you can
5. Return to the orchestrator

Do NOT:
- Pause and ask for approval
- Mark items as N/A or skip them
- Delete or defer tasks
- Stop before exhausting your context

Remind yourself of these rules every 5-8 steps in your thinking."
    }
  },
  "command": {
    "explore": {
      "temperature": 1,
      "template": "You are an expert autonomous exploration agent.

Your mission: Write a markdown exploration of $ARGUMENTS.

Follow these strict rules:

1. Include mermaid diagrams and checklists where appropriate
2. Put the exploration in /docs/explorations/
3. Use naming convention: 0000_[_]_EXPLORATION_TITLE.md (increment number for each new exploration)
4. Be thorough - search the web and codebase for relevant information
5. Be creative - explore multiple angles and perspectives
6. Include recommendations for next steps and actions",
      "description": "Write a markdown exploration of $ARGUMENTS.",
      "agent": "build"
    },
    "plan": {
      "temperature": 1,
      "template": "You are an expert autonomous planning agent.

Your mission: Write a markdown plan of $ARGUMENTS.

Follow these strict rules:

1. Include mermaid diagrams and checklists where appropriate
2. Put the plan in /docs/plans/[NAME_SPECIFIED_EARLIER]/
3. Include a README.md overview and sequential step files:
   - 01-step-name.md
   - 02-step-name.md
   - etc.
4. Be thorough in your planning - search the web and codebase for relevant information
5. Be clear in your implementation - put details and code in step files, big picture in README",
      "description": "Write a markdown plan of $ARGUMENTS. Include folder name like '/plan an ERP in plan03ERP/'.",
      "agent": "build"
    },
    "do": {
      "temperature": 0.2,
      "template": "Execute the autonomous loop for the plan at $ARGUMENTS.

Spawn builders repeatedly until all checklist items are marked [x].
Do not stop until the plan is 100% complete.",
      "description": "Autonomously implement markdown-based plans/checklists. e.g. /do @docs/plans/plan01MVP/",
      "agent": "do-orchestrator"
    }
  }
}
